In [[agriculture]] '''cultural control''' is the practice of modifying the growing environment to reduce the prevalence of unwanted [[pest (animal)|pest]]s. Examples include changing soil [[pH]] or [[fertility]] levels, [[irrigation]] practices, amount of sunlight, temperature, or the use of beneficial animals (e.g. chickens) or insects (e.g. ladybugs) (biological control). Using cultural control before chemical control can reduce detrimental effects to the ecosystem surrounding the growing environment. 

