'''Freezing toilet''' is a kind of [[dry toilet]] based on [[electricity]] which freezes the content in a short time.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.ess.fi/teemat/koti/2015/05/13/kakalle-pakastimeen-jaatynyt-jatos-ei-haise|title=Kakalle pakastimeen, jäätynyt jätös ei haise|author=Satu Vikström|date=2015-05-13|publisher= [[Etelä-Suomen Sanomat]]|language =Finnish|trans-title=What kind of freezer, frozen waste does not smell|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20171214152722/http://www.ess.fi/teemat/koti/2015/05/13/kakalle-pakastimeen-jaatynyt-jatos-ei-haise|archivedate=2017-12-14|accessdate=2017-12-14}}</ref> Freezing toilets work by electricity, as they are plugged into the wall. They do not need water, pipes, ventilation or chemicals to work.
The function of freezing toilets is based on freezing. The contents freeze in a short time stopping bacteria from growing and keeping it odourless. Consequently, it doesn't need mixtures or other chemicals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huussi.net/en/materials/dry-toilet-conferences/dry-toilet-conference-2012/full-papers/|title=Full papers - Käymäläseura Huussi|work=huussi.net}}</ref>

Freezing toilets can be moved, as they only need a plug to work. The machine consumes about 40 watts of electricity.{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}

Freezing toilets were developed in [[Sweden]] in the 1970s, but now production is in [[Finland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gizmodo.com/5898384/toilet-freezes-your-poop-to-keep-it-from-stinking|title=Toilet Freezes Your Poop To Keep It From Stinking|author=Mario Aguilar|work=Gizmodo|publisher=Gawker Media|accessdate=16 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huussi.net/en/materials/literature/|title=Literature - Käymäläseura Huussi|work=huussi.net}}</ref> 

== Examples ==
This kind of toilet is installed at the Mirrorcube treeroom at ''Treehotel'' ([[Harads]], Sweden).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/yjeanmundelsalle/2016/05/19/feel-like-a-kid-again-and-live-in-a-treehouse-when-you-stay-at-the-stylish-treehotel-in-sweden/|title=Feel Like A Kid Again In This Stylish Treehotel In Sweden|author=Y-Jean Mun-Delsalle|date=2016-05-19|publisher=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=2017-12-14}}</ref>

